<:f240,2Tms Rmn,0,0,0>POINTSZ

<:f240,2Tms Rmn,0,0,0>This is the test document for point size in 
Ami Pro.

<:f240,2Tms Rmn,0,0,0>

<:f160,2Tms Rmn,0,0,0>This text is in 8 point.  It's a wonder we didn't 
lose our minds, given the outrageous premise of a TV program that 
promised identical cousins.  What isn't surprising is that the producers 
made sure the song prefaced every episode of the Patty Duke Show, 
since it explained the relationship between the two girls.

<:f160,2Tms Rmn,0,0,0>Still 8 point.  Cathy, brought up in England 
and "abroad," had a posh accent and fancy tastes (for crepes suzette), 
in contrast to Patty, who chewed gum incessantly and could be counted 
on to mess up at least once during every program.

